What is so great about this project?

By 2025, pure drinking water deficiency on earth will have grown up to 1.3-2.0 trillion cubic meters per year. China, Southeast Asia, Middle East and Africa will be the first to encounter severe fresh water shortage.

BAIKALIKA extracts the deep-layer water from the Lake Baikal and works on the promotion of BAIKALIKA in the most water-deficient regions in the world.

Thus, Baikalika project has great potential for providing a stable supply of pure drinking water to consumers and also offers a great opportunity for the BAIKALIKA token holders to obtain substantial profits

What else do you need to know?

Experienced water producer

Baikalika already mines and sells the water from Baikal. The funding will be used to expand the scope of operations to supply token-holders.

Advanced technology

Blockchain solution for the BAIKALIKA tokens operations managed via smart contracts and based on the proof of stake model, guarantees transparency and safety for the BAIKALIKA tokens holders.

The token value set to grow

The buy-back program for token holders assumes that the volume of the tokens available on the market will decrease with the time thus impacting positively on the tokens’ price and liquidity.

How it works for tokens-holders

Baikalika accumulates pure Baikal water on behalf of a token holder and delivers it to a warehouse in China, Southeast Asia, the Middle East or elsewhere.

Token holder

The token holder gets the following benefits:

  1. Personal water consumption
  2. The option to sell the water to a retail store or
    to Baikalika

Pure Drinking Water

BAIKALIKA water is extracted three kilometers (about 1.6 miles) away from the shore, and from a 400-meter (about 0.22 miles) depth. This fresh drinking water is untouched by human civilization, is unique in its purity, and has been acknowledged as etalon drinking water.

This water features the best combination of water’s properties: ﬂawless purity, high saturation with hydrogen and oxygen, no heavy metals present, and Ph in line with human blood.

Currently, Baikal is listed as a UNESCO World Heritage Site, and is a world-known brand.

BAIKALIKA production is environmentally sound, which is confirmed by our holding of all of the relevant licenses and certificates. From each recovered liter of the Baikal water, BAIKALIKA will be allocating a certain part of its profit into both non-governmental and governmental entities for the preservation and developmental growth of the Baikal natural territory and lake Baikal.

Project roadmap

Currently, the amount of Baikal water produced by the Baikalika plant is 8.5 million liters per year. The water is supplied to the Russian market.

The purpose of the Crowdsale is to raise funds for the plant output expansion and for the marketing of product information to water-deficient countries, in the first place –to China. In the long term, it is planned to increase the volume of the supplied product and to enter the markets of South-Eastern Asia and the Middle East.
